abstract: Anthony Comello is obsessed with conspiracy theories. His paranoia is being litigated in a Staten Island court.
snippet: Anthony Comello is obsessed with conspiracy theories. His paranoia is being litigated in a Staten Island court.
lead_paragraph: Four days after pulling off the most high-profile mob killing in decades, Anthony Comello sat down with New York Police Department detectives and told them that the C.I.A. had infiltrated the Mafia. And, he added, the government was spying on him.

abstract: At congressional hearings, protests and even over pizza, some background players are finding momentary fame.
snippet: At congressional hearings, protests and even over pizza, some background players are finding momentary fame.
lead_paragraph: No matter the job title, the gig of most every aide to a member of Congress is essentially the same: to help make it appear that the elected representative — “the name on the door,” as some aides put it — is shouldering the work alone.

abstract: It’s about time, the late-night hosts said on Thursday, after Speaker Nancy Pelosi finally announced the drafting of articles of impeachment against President Trump.

abstract: The Labor Department’s report was much stronger than the one last month, helped by the end of a General Motors strike.
snippet: The Labor Department’s report was much stronger than the one last month, helped by the end of a General Motors strike.
lead_paragraph: America’s job engine has again defied jittery stock traders, bearish forecasters and blue-ribbon economists to deliver eye-catching gains and power an exceptionally resilient economy.

abstract: A big announcement by Nancy Pelosi — and a contentious news conference afterward.
snippet: A big announcement by Nancy Pelosi — and a contentious news conference afterward.
lead_paragraph: A few hours after Ms. Pelosi’s announcement, she held a second news conference, where she got into a contentious exchange with a reporter — one that Julie Davis, our congressional editor, explored on “The Latest,” our impeachment podcast.

abstract: Nine months ago, the speaker said President Trump was “just not worth it.” Then she saw an explosive headline.
snippet: Nine months ago, the speaker said President Trump was “just not worth it.” Then she saw an explosive headline.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi was planning to deliver back-to-back eulogies at funerals here and in South Carolina during a busy weekend of late September travel when she saw an explosive headline in The Wall Street Journal: “Trump Repeatedly Pressed Ukraine to Investigate Biden’s Son.”

abstract: The State Department’s estimate of casualties from the current protests in Iran is higher than other, independent tallies.
snippet: The State Department’s estimate of casualties from the current protests in Iran is higher than other, independent tallies.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In a rare rebuke of Iran after more than a year of trying to bridge the divisions between Washington and Tehran, three European powers accused Iran of testing ballistic missiles intended to avoid missile defenses in violation of United Nations resolutions that urge Iran not to develop “nuclear capable” systems.
